Constable Enkosi Matiwane allegedly raped a woman who'd been arrested for shoplifting in a holding cell at the Grassy Park Police Station three years ago. CAPE TOWN - A police officer accused of rape has been dismissed. Constable Enkosi Matiwane allegedly raped a woman who'd been arrested for shoplifting in a holding cell at the Grassy Park Police Station three years ago. Matiwane appeared in court on Monday. The official was fired after an internal disciplinary hearing found him guilty.